channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Pro-Palestinian protests disrupt colleges across the US
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests are disrupting major US universities, and several schools have called police to remove demonstrators. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Likely attack by Yemen's Houthi rebels targets a vessel in the Red Sea
item.description: A suspected missile attack by Yemen’s Houthi rebels targeted a container in the Red Sea, the latest assault in their campaign against international shipping in the crucial maritime route

item.title: April 28, 2024 - US university protests
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at major US universities, and several schools have called police to remove demonstrators.

item.title: 40 people die in western Kenya after a dam collapses
item.description: Police in Kenya say at least 40 people have died after a dam collapsed in the country’s west

item.title: April 27, 2024 - Campus protest updates
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at major US universities, where several schools have called police on protesters, leading to the arrests of hundreds across the country. Follow for live updates.

item.title: College protests live updates: Police crackdown leads to hundreds of arrests
item.description: Protests have broken out at colleges and universities across the country in connection with the war in Gaza.

item.title: April 26, 2024 - Protests at Columbia and other schools escalate
item.description: Pro-Palestinian protests continue at major US universities where several schools have called police on protesters, leading to the arrests of hundreds across the country. Follow for live updates.

item.title: Teens plotted to buy guns, attack Jewish people after Sydney stabbing: police
item.description: Police allege in court documents that four teenagers plotted to buy guns and attack Jewish people days after a Christian bishop was stabbed in a Sydney church

item.title: Day 8 of Trump New York hush money trial
item.description: Ex-tabloid publisher David Pecker and Donald Trump's former assistant Rhona Graff were among those who testifed Friday in the hush money trial.

item.title: Tesla founder Elon Musk visits China as competitors show off new electric vehicles
item.description: Tesla founder and CEO Elon Musk has met with a top government leader in the Chinese capital, just as the nation’s carmakers are showing off their latest electric vehicle models at the Beijing auto show
